				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-pet/1.16?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Pet. 1:16</a>; see also <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/lev/11.44-45?lang=eng#43" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Lev. 11:44&ndash;45</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/lev/19.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Lev. 19:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/lev/20.26?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Lev. 20:26</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-95911_000_035">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.27?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 27:27</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-95911_000_035">36.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See Neal A. Maxwell, <span class="emphasis">We Talk of Christ, We Rejoice in Christ</span> (Salt Lake City: Deseret Book Co., 1984), p. 145; Hugh B. Brown, <span class="emphasis">The Abundant Life</span> (Salt Lake City: Bookcraft, 1965), p. 199.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-95911_000_035">37.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/12.48?lang=eng#47" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 12:48</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-95911_000_035">38.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/4.12-13?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Eph. 4:12&ndash;13</a>; emphasis added.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-95911_000_035">39.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.32-33?lang=eng#31" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moro. 10:32&ndash;33</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-95911_000_035">40.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/67.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 67:13</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-95911_000_035">41.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.19?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 132:19</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-95911_000_035"><a name="-95911_000_035">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote42-95911_000_035">42.</a>
      </span>
				<p>This concept is supported by the fact that in verses of the New Testament that refer to the <span class="emphasis">end</span> for which we are to endure, the Greek word from which <span class="emphasis">end</span> was translated was also derived from <span class="emphasis">telos</span> (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/10.22?lang=eng#21" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matt. 10:22</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/24.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matt. 24:13</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/13.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mark 13:13</a>).</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
                                        
